The '''[[Houston Astros]]' [[1980 Major League Baseball season|1980 season]]''' was a season in American baseball. It involved the Houston Astros attempting to win the [[National League West]].

==Regular season==
* [[July 4]], [[1980]]: Nolan Ryan got the 3000th strikeout of his career by striking out [[Cesar Geronimo]] of the [[1980 Cincinnati Reds season|Cincinnati Reds]].

